    <item>
      <title>About</title>
      <link>https://ayushkcs.com/about/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ayushkcs.com/about/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://ayushkcs.com/static/Images/about.jpeg&#34; alt=&#34;About&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;in this small corner of the web, let me share a bit of my story.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;i&amp;rsquo;m ayush.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;yeah, like the kid in the picture above, i&amp;rsquo;ve always been this curious kid, wandering about the complexity of this world, tinkering here and there. now, i explore the world through words and code.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;i&amp;rsquo;ve always wanted to study arts and humanities, but destiny had some other plans. here i am on the verge of graduating with a CS degree. honestly, i didn&amp;rsquo;t like it initially, but now i have started loving it. i feel like i&amp;rsquo;m a walking paradox; i love poetry and art as much as i love science and deep tech.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
